  "prompt": "Are there laws that prevent the disguise of illicit funds?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have anti-money laundering (AML) laws designed to prevent the disguise or concealment of illicit funds. These laws typically require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Conduct customer due diligence\n2. Report suspicious transactions\n3. Maintain transaction records\n4. Verify the source of funds\n5. Implement compliance programs to detect potential money laundering\n\nIn the US, key legislation includes the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act, which establish requirements for identifying and reporting suspicious financial activities.",
